The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Two men were killed and another was injured in mishaps in the city on Monday. A physically challenged man, riding a tricycle, died after being knocked down by a trailer (NL-01D 1223) in Garden Reach on Monday morning. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared dead on arrival. In another accident, an unidentified man in his 30s was killed when a trailer hit his bike on National Highway 6, in Howrahs Panchla, around 5pm.  middle-aged man was injured after falling off a private bus on route 221 at the Rashbehari Avenue-Sarat Bose Road crossing around 10.22am. B.K. Roy was taken to RK Mission Seva Pratisthan and later shifted to SSKM Hospital. The driver has been arrested.  rishna Adak, a 32-year-old cyclist who was knocked down by an Ambassador in Salt Lake on Sunday, died early on Monday.    The high court on Monday asked Kamarhati Municipality to demolish a temple being built illegally near BT Road in Belghoria by May 24. The verdict came after a petition by Sipra Dutta, a local resident, who alleged that the structure, coming up in the middle of a 20ft wide road at Amritnagar in Belghoria, was illegal and had blocked half the road. Justice G.C. Gupta also asked the superintendent of North 24-Parganas police to deploy personnel in the area when the structure would be razed.    A man in his 20s was found dead near Bank Plot in Kasba on Monday morning. The body has been sent for post-mortem.     A 35-year-old man was injured after being attacked and shot at by four men near his Garden Reach house on Monday evening. Police said the four first attacked Akhtar Ali, a worker, with a chopper and then fired two bullets which hit him in the right hand. Local people took him to CMRI. His condition was critical.    The body of a woman was exhumed on Monday morning after residents spotted some bones jutting out of the ground in Jafarpur, Barasat. The corpse has been sent for post-mortem.    The condition of CPM legislator Chandana Ghosh Dastidar, who was admitted to RN Tagore hospital on Sunday, was stable, doctors said on Monday. She was allegedly assaulted by Trinamul supporters in Falta. Seven Trinamul supporters arrested in this connection were granted bail on Monday.     Anthony Arun Biswas is contesting from Calcutta South and not Calcutta North as mentioned in the report Band of outsiders with bat, torch and candle published in Metro on May 11. The error is regretted.                                                                                                                                                                   
